{
  "message": "fix(fuzz,ci): add workspace key to fuzz crate, enable --all-targets, update conformance snapshots\n\nThree related infrastructure fixes:\n\n1. crates/frankenlibc-fuzz/Cargo.toml: Add [workspace] section so\n   cargo-fuzz treats the fuzz crate as its own workspace root, preventing\n   'current package believes it's in a workspace' errors when running\n   cargo fuzz from the subcrate directory.\n\n2. scripts/ci.sh: Change 'cargo test --workspace' to\n   'cargo test --workspace --all-targets' so integration tests in\n   tests/ directories and benches are compiled and run alongside unit\n   tests, catching link errors and ABI regressions that unit-only runs\n   would miss (like the new stdlib_abi_test.rs).\n\n3. Conformance JSON snapshots regenerated with current timestamps and\n   updated string family coverage data:\n   - fuzz_phase1_targets: string family now lists 22 available symbols\n     (was 17) after adding stpcpy, stpncpy, strchrnul, strncmp, strnlen;\n     covered_count=18, coverage_pct drops to 81.8% reflecting honest\n     accounting of newly-tracked but not-yet-fuzzed symbols.\n   - fuzz_harness_architecture and fuzz_membrane_validation: timestamp\n     refresh only (no structural changes).\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
